You are an independent skeptic verifying another agent's investigation of the RBK "Lode" subsystem (fetched-side artifact capture into GAR), in the repo at the current working directory. Do NOT trust their summary — RE-READ the cited files yourself.

Their area: cutover (cutover chokepoints / bole timing)

Their findings (JSON):
[
  {
    "claim": "The conjure base FROM coordinate is derived in exactly ONE chokepoint, zrbfd_stitch_build_json, and the election variable is the per-slot RBRV_IMAGE_n_ANCHOR. If ANCHOR is set, the base ref resolves to ${gar_repo_base}/<pkg>:<tag> (a GAR locator); if empty, ORIGIN passes through to upstream. This is the single seam a bole cutover repoints.",
    "evidence": "Tools/rbk/rbfd_FoundryDirectorBuild.sh:437-466 — loop over slots 1-3: 'if test -n \"${z_ri_anchor}\"' resolves z_ri_ref=\"${z_gar_repo_base}/${z_ri_pkg_path}:${z_ri_tag}\" else z_ri_ref=\"${z_ri_origin}\"; comment line 424 'Resolve base images: ANCHOR (locator) -> full GAR reference, or pass ORIGIN through.'",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "claim": "The landed ensconce (bole) capture ALREADY emits the exact coordinate enshrine produces — its in-package member tag is literally annotated as the legacy enshrine anchor — so repointing the base derived-pull at the ensconce capture-file is a coordinate substitution, not a new computation. The bole capture-file (one per Lode, keyed by touchmark) carries the vouch envelope with origin + digest the host writes via buf_write_fact_multi.",
    "evidence": "Tools/rbk/rbgjl/rbgjl01-ensconce-capture.sh:20 '#   :<sanitized-origin>-<sha10>      UNSPRUED — name + glance-fingerprint (= legacy enshrine anchor)'; capture-file written at Tools/rbk/rbldb_Bole.sh:135 'buf_write_fact_multi \"${z_stamp}\" \"${RBCC_fact_ext_lode}\" \"${z_vouch}\"'",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "claim": "BOLE-CUTOVER IS INDEPENDENT of every other kind vertical. Bole ensconce reads only RBRV_IMAGE_n_ORIGIN (the same input enshrine reads) and rides the already-landed spine (rblds_Spine.sh) + bole body (rbldb_Bole.sh). Nothing in the base-capture or base-resolution path touches the tool/reliquary/wsl/podvm kinds. The only precursor it needs — ensconce — is landed.",
    "evidence": "Tools/rbk/rbldb_Bole.sh:164-170 resolves base via RBRV_IMAGE_n_ORIGIN; rbldb_Bole.sh:93-96 dispatches through zrbld_spine_dispatch (landed spine); rbfd_FoundryDirectorBuild.sh:308-315 and 437-442 the enshrine derived-pull keys off the same RBRV_IMAGE_n_ORIGIN/ANCHOR pair",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "claim": "RELIQUARY-CUTOVER IS NOT independent — it requires the conclave (reliquary-kind, N-member date-cohort) vertical to exist first. The reliquary election variable RBRV_RELIQUARY feeds the single tool-resolution chokepoint zrbfc_resolve_tool_images, which fans the six tool images (gcloud/docker/alpine/syft/binfmt/skopeo) into conjure, about, vouch, enshrine, AND the bole ensconce itself. A reliquary is an N-tool cohort under one datestamp — exactly the conclave kind's multi-member shape — so you cannot repoint RBRV_RELIQUARY onto a Lode until a Lode of that cardinality (conclave) can be captured.",
    "evidence": "Tools/rbk/rbfca_StepAssembly.sh:32-46 zrbfc_resolve_tool_images reads RBRV_RELIQUARY (line 35) and emits z_rbfc_tool_{gcloud,docker,alpine,syft,binfmt,skopeo}; consumed at rbfd_FoundryDirectorBuild.sh:912/1229/1397/1669, rbfv_FoundryVerify.sh:593, and rbldb_Bole.sh:185; reliquary is the date-cohort tool set per Tools/rbk/rbfli_Inscribe.sh:144 z_reliquary='r'+stamp with six RBGC_RELIQUARY_TOOL_* members",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "claim": "The two paths have genuinely DISTINCT, non-overlapping election variables, which is what makes them severable: bole-cutover repoints RBRV_IMAGE_n_ANCHOR (per-base, conjure FROM coordinate); reliquary-cutover repoints RBRV_RELIQUARY (per-vessel, the builder-image set). They live in the same regime (RBSRV) but in different variable groups and feed different chokepoints.",
    "evidence": "Tools/rbk/vov_veiled/RBSRV-RegimeVessel.adoc:54-59 rbrv_group_reliquary -> RBRV_RELIQUARY ('applies to every vessel'); RBSRV:121-154 rbrv_group_image -> RBRV_IMAGE_n_ORIGIN/ANCHOR ('rbtgo_ark_enshrine resolves each ORIGIN to a GAR-mirrored ANCHOR')",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "claim": "Concrete bole-cutover repoint steps: (a) retire enshrine's writer rbfd_enshrine / zrbfd_enshrine_submit / zrbfd_enshrine_extract_anchors (rbfd_FoundryDirectorBuild.sh:883+) and its tabtarget rbw-dE (tt/rbw-dE.DirectorEnshrinesVessel.sh); (b) have the ANCHOR-population path write the bole Lode coordinate from the ensconce capture-file instead of the rbi_es anchor; (c) leave the conjure consumer at rbfd_FoundryDirectorBuild.sh:445-455 unchanged since it consumes whatever locator sits in RBRV_IMAGE_n_ANCHOR. Verify-gate: one airgap conjure build green (the airgap path is the strict consumer — empty anchor fails loud at rbfd:321-348), since tether conjure tolerates pass-through and would mask a broken anchor.",
    "evidence": "Tools/rbk/rbfd_FoundryDirectorBuild.sh:883-938 rbfd_enshrine; tt/rbw-dE.DirectorEnshrinesVessel.sh; airgap strictness at rbfd_FoundryDirectorBuild.sh:321-348 'Airgap conjure cannot reach upstream — base images must be enshrined first'",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "claim": "Enshrine has secondary consumers beyond the conjure chokepoint that the bole cutover must also repoint or retire: the theurge onboarding harness (rbtdro_enshrine, RBTDGC_VERB_ENSHRINE) drives airgap fixtures through enshrine, and the airgap handbook (rbhoda_director_airgap.sh) hardcodes rbi_es anchors in operator instructions. These are real but mechanical follow-ons, not new dependencies on other kind verticals.",
    "evidence": "Tools/rbk/rbtd/src/rbtdro_onboarding.rs:366-370 rbtdro_enshrine + rbtdgc_consts.rs:136 RBTDGC_VERB_ENSHRINE; Tools/rbk/rbh0/rbhoda_director_airgap.sh:167 'RBRV_IMAGE_1_ANCHOR=rbi_es/rust-slim-bookworm-...'",
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
  {
    "claim": "GAR namespace banished LAST per path: the rbi_es (enshrine) namespace is banished only after the bole cutover proves green and no writer/reader remains; rbi_rq (reliquary) is banished only after the conclave cutover repoints RBRV_RELIQUARY onto a reliquary-kind Lode. Each namespace is an independent flat sibling under the GAR repo, so banishing one does not disturb the other.",
    "evidence": "Tools/rbk/rbgc_Constants.sh:206-209 rbi_rq/rbi_es/rbi_ld as peer RBGC_GAR_CATEGORY_* constants; rbi_es read sites enumerated at rbgc_Constants.sh:207, rbfd_FoundryDirectorBuild.sh:426, rbflw_Wrest.sh:34; reliquary read chokepoint at rbfca_StepAssembly.sh:39",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "claim": "Doing bole-cutover before the other verticals exist carries ONE real risk vector and it is contained: bole-cutover does NOT remove the reliquary dependency. The bole ensconce itself still calls zrbfc_resolve_tool_images (needs skopeo+docker from rbi_rq). So bole-cutover retires rbi_es but leaves rbi_rq fully live — correct and intended, since reliquary retirement is the separate conclave-gated cutover. No risk of orphaning the tool path.",
    "evidence": "Tools/rbk/rbldb_Bole.sh:184-185 '# Resolve tool images from reliquary (skopeo for capture, docker for vouch).' then 'zrbfc_resolve_tool_images'; recipe at rbldb_Bole.sh:55-58 uses ${z_rbfc_tool_skopeo} and ${z_rbfc_tool_docker}",
    "confidence": "high"
  }
]

Their recommendation_input:
SLATE THE BOLE-CUTOVER EARLY (immediately after scaffold), do NOT pair it with the reliquary cutover. The two cutovers are severable because they have distinct election variables feeding distinct chokepoints, and they retire distinct GAR namespaces.

Dependency reasoning: The bole-cutover's only precursor — the ensconce verb — is already LANDED (rbldb_Bole.sh on the rblds_Spine.sh). The base FROM coordinate is derived in a single chokepoint (zrbfd_stitch_build_json, rbfd:437-466) keyed on RBRV_IMAGE_n_ANCHOR, and the landed ensconce capture already emits the byte-equivalent coordinate — its member tag is literally annotated '(= legacy enshrine anchor)' at rbgjl01-ensconce-capture.sh:20. So the cutover is a coordinate-source substitution (read the bole capture-file instead of writing an rbi_es anchor), needing nothing from the tool/reliquary/wsl/podvm verticals.

By contrast the reliquary-cutover is genuinely gated on the conclave vertical: RBRV_RELIQUARY feeds zrbfc_resolve_tool_images (rbfca:32-47), the six-tool date-cohort is exactly conclave's N-member shape, and that chokepoint is consumed by conjure/about/vouch/enshrine AND bole ensconce. You cannot repoint RBRV_RELIQUARY onto a Lode until a multi-member (conclave) Lode can be captured. Pairing bole with reliquary as 'siblings' would needlessly block the independent, low-risk bole win behind the conclave build.

Risk of doing bole-cutover before other verticals exist: essentially none, and notably bole-cutover does NOT strand the tool path — bole ensconce still resolves skopeo/docker from the live reliquary (rbldb_Bole.sh:185), so retiring rbi_es leaves rbi_rq correctly intact for the later conclave-gated reliquary cutover. The only follow-on work is mechanical: repoint/retire enshrine's secondary consumers (theurge rbtdro_enshrine airgap fixtures, the rbi_es-hardcoded airgap handbook rbhoda) and delete tabtarget rbw-dE. Gate: one AIRGAP conjure build green (airgap is the strict anchor consumer at rbfd:321-348; tether pass-through would mask a broken anchor). Banish rbi_es LAST, after green + zero residual readers.

Independently check the LOAD-BEARING factual claims against the actual files. For each, return whether it holds (with a note citing what you found). Then — most important — state in `corrections` anything they got WRONG, any citation that's off, or anything they MISSED that would change the recommendation. If the recommendation stands as-is, set corrections to an empty string.

